WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:03.090
- Thanks for coming.

00:05.179 --> 00:08.573
- All right, birthday girl.
One more drink.

00:08.617 --> 00:10.836
- I actually need to go home,
Becca.

00:10.880 --> 00:12.838
My kids--
- Are at a sleepover.

00:12.882 --> 00:15.276
And Sonny's game
is still going at the Garden.

00:15.319 --> 00:17.495
- I know--if I leave now,

00:17.539 --> 00:20.063
I'll be able to catch
the last few minutes on TV.

00:20.107 --> 00:22.718
- That's why God created
"SportsCenter" for, babe.

00:22.761 --> 00:23.849
Come on.

00:23.893 --> 00:25.808
Morty's is, like,
half a block away.

00:25.851 --> 00:27.549
- I'm really not in the mood.

00:27.592 --> 00:30.334
- Did you forget to read
your own "Vogue" cover?

00:30.378 --> 00:33.294
35 is the new 25.

00:33.337 --> 00:34.860
- I know.

00:34.904 --> 00:39.213
Yeah, apparently.
[chuckling]

00:39.256 --> 00:40.649
- Home, Mrs. Langer?

00:40.692 --> 00:43.739
- Can you hold your horses?
One drink.

00:43.782 --> 00:45.393
- It's never one drink
with you.

00:45.436 --> 00:47.221
We had Bellinis at the house

00:47.264 --> 00:48.396
then had two bottles
of red at dinner.

00:48.439 --> 00:49.701
- Exactly.

00:49.745 --> 00:52.791
So now it is time
for espresso martinis.

00:52.835 --> 00:54.184
What're you gonna do,

00:54.228 --> 00:56.621
go home to that big,
empty house all alone?

00:56.665 --> 00:58.275
- You're relentless.
- Yes.

00:58.319 --> 01:00.364
I knew you'd come around.

01:00.408 --> 01:02.236
- Morty's, Ernie.

01:04.281 --> 01:05.543
- Lasagna's awesome, mom.

01:05.587 --> 01:07.197
It's nice to finally have
a home-cooked meal.

01:07.241 --> 01:09.112
- What are you talking about?
I cook all the time.

01:09.156 --> 01:12.115
- Dad, spaghetti, burgers,
and hot dogs isn't cooking.

01:12.159 --> 01:14.639
- Sure it is.
All the major food groups.

01:14.683 --> 01:17.860
You know what?
Let's say a blessing.

01:17.903 --> 01:19.209
- We don't do that anymore.
- Why?

01:19.253 --> 01:20.906
- I know, maybe we should,
you know.

01:20.950 --> 01:22.386
For old time's sake.

01:22.430 --> 01:24.519
- Good idea.

01:24.562 --> 01:27.261
Come on, come on. Let's do it.

01:31.961 --> 01:34.268
- God is great.
God is good.

01:34.311 --> 01:36.226
all: Let us thank him
for this food.

01:36.270 --> 01:37.227
Amen.

01:37.271 --> 01:38.750
- Oh, hang on. I have a PS.

01:38.794 --> 01:39.751
- Dad, you can't
PS a blessing--

01:39.795 --> 01:41.405
- Come on. Just humor me.

01:41.449 --> 01:43.538
Thank you also for this family

01:43.581 --> 01:45.409
and for this time
to be together.

01:45.453 --> 01:47.672
Amen.
- Amen.

01:47.716 --> 01:49.674
- So you think
God can give me

01:49.718 --> 01:51.589
notes on my college essay?
It's due next week.

01:51.633 --> 01:53.156
- There we go.
- Oh, my--

01:53.200 --> 01:55.158
- It's going to be great,
and I can't wait to read it.

01:55.202 --> 01:56.594
- Seriously, though,
I need help.

01:56.638 --> 01:58.509
[laughter]
- You don't need help.

01:58.553 --> 02:00.511
I know you don't need help.

02:05.821 --> 02:08.432
- Here's good. Thanks.

02:08.476 --> 02:12.567
- You need help getting inside?
Mrs. Langer?

02:12.610 --> 02:16.179
- I'm a pro in heels.
Have a good night.

02:16.223 --> 02:17.528
- Good night.

02:17.572 --> 02:20.531
[unsettling music]

02:20.575 --> 02:27.582
♪

02:46.818 --> 02:48.864
[door clicks open]

02:48.907 --> 02:50.735
Hello?

02:53.738 --> 02:56.393
[floorboards creak]

02:56.437 --> 02:58.352
Is someone there?

03:00.658 --> 03:01.833
Hello?

03:07.883 --> 03:12.670
- Hello? Mrs. Esme?

03:12.714 --> 03:14.846
I'm here.

03:28.295 --> 03:30.949
[tense music]

03:30.993 --> 03:36.303
♪

03:36.346 --> 03:39.436
[screaming]

03:48.097 --> 03:49.446
- Wow.

03:49.490 --> 03:52.362
Our victim
is Sonny Langer's wife.

03:52.406 --> 03:53.711
- She's a successful
businesswoman

03:53.755 --> 03:55.583
who made "Fortune's"
"40 Under 40" last year,

03:55.626 --> 03:57.933
but Sonny Langer's wife.
Sure.

03:57.976 --> 03:59.717
- Her name's Esme Langer.

03:59.761 --> 04:01.980
Supermodel
turned lifestyle guru,

04:02.024 --> 04:03.852
murdered last night
after dinner with friends

04:03.895 --> 04:05.723
to celebrate her 35th birthday.

04:05.767 --> 04:07.725
- So media pressure
makes this our case?

04:07.769 --> 04:10.598
- PD asked for all hands on.
So did Isobel.

04:10.641 --> 04:13.296
Murder of a celebrity
is front-page news.

04:13.340 --> 04:15.603
When that celebrity's
married to a basketball star?

04:15.646 --> 04:17.300
- It's a national event.

04:17.344 --> 04:19.389
- Looks like the scuffle
started in the bedroom.

04:19.433 --> 04:21.913
- And ended up
behind the couch,

04:21.957 --> 04:27.310
where she was stabbed multiple
times through the neck.

04:27.354 --> 04:30.313
[suspenseful music]

04:30.357 --> 04:34.361
♪

04:34.404 --> 04:36.928
That's, uh--
- Yeah.

04:36.972 --> 04:39.540
- She was decapitated.
- Nearly.

04:39.583 --> 04:41.019
The housekeeper
found the body this morning

04:41.063 --> 04:42.804
and accidentally
finished the job.

04:42.847 --> 04:45.633
Detective Lee, Greenwich PD.
We appreciate the help.

04:45.676 --> 04:47.330
- Any prints?

04:47.374 --> 04:49.550
- Only partials.
No murder weapon either.

04:49.593 --> 04:50.986
- Seems odd for a crime scene
this messy.

04:51.029 --> 04:52.335
- A bit.

04:52.379 --> 04:54.729
- But also consistent
with a possible robbery.

04:54.772 --> 04:56.731
Woman catches
a robber mid-theft,

04:56.774 --> 04:58.602
the guy freaks out, kills her,

04:58.646 --> 05:00.604
wipes his prints,
and then runs.

05:00.648 --> 05:02.171
- What'd they steal?

05:02.214 --> 05:04.391
- According to the housekeeper,
most of Sonny's career.

05:04.434 --> 05:10.005
Framed jerseys, game balls,
trophies, his MVP rings.

05:10.048 --> 05:12.486
- These memorabilia must
be worth a fortune.

05:12.529 --> 05:14.575
- And must be insured.

05:14.618 --> 05:16.359
Let's check with
the homeowners' carrier,

05:16.403 --> 05:19.101
see if they have photographs
of anything that was taken.

05:19.144 --> 05:21.582
- Anything else missing?
- Not that we can tell.

05:21.625 --> 05:23.453
Looks like our killer
tampered with the bedroom safe

05:23.497 --> 05:26.369
but couldn't get it open.

05:26.413 --> 05:28.458
- What you thinking?

05:28.502 --> 05:31.156
- Just a sequined party dress
and $800 heels?

05:31.200 --> 05:32.549
Esme was a fashion icon.

05:32.593 --> 05:34.072
Why wasn't she wearing
any jewelry?

05:34.116 --> 05:35.813
- Killer could have
taken that too.

05:35.857 --> 05:37.815
Might need to ask the husband.

05:37.859 --> 05:39.426
- Apparently, he stayed
in the city last night

05:39.469 --> 05:40.731
in his suite at the Ritz.

05:40.775 --> 05:42.820
Kids were at a sleepover
while Mom went out.

05:42.864 --> 05:44.996
- Sonny has an alibi.
- Who?

05:45.040 --> 05:47.999
- Me and 20,000
other Knicks fans.

05:48.043 --> 05:49.740
He had a game
at the Garden last night.

05:49.784 --> 05:51.960
- You were there?
- No, I watched it on TV.

05:52.003 --> 05:53.396
I've been following Sonny

05:53.440 --> 05:55.398
since he got drafted
by the Clippers out of Hudson.

05:55.442 --> 05:57.531
Three years in LA,
six years with the Knicks

05:57.574 --> 05:59.837
before he retired
four years ago.

05:59.881 --> 06:01.056
He decided he wanted
to play again.

06:01.099 --> 06:03.188
Last night was
his third game back.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.929
- If the kids were
at a sleepover,

06:04.973 --> 06:06.888
that means the last person
to see Esme alive

06:06.931 --> 06:09.499
was the limo driver.
Let's check into him.

06:09.543 --> 06:13.111
Let's see if we can tap
into Esme's cell phone.

06:13.155 --> 06:16.550
- If Sonny's guilty,
he's gonna lawyer up.

06:16.593 --> 06:18.813
- Probably.

06:18.856 --> 06:20.989
That's why you and I
are heading to the hotel

06:21.032 --> 06:22.556
before the circus
comes to town.

06:23.818 --> 06:26.821
[reporters chattering]

06:33.610 --> 06:36.047
- So you and your agent,
Mr. Styles here...

06:36.091 --> 06:38.223
- Call me Bronson, please.

06:38.267 --> 06:41.096
- Went straight to dinner
right after the game.

06:41.139 --> 06:42.663
Can anyone confirm that?

06:42.706 --> 06:45.535
- 100 cameras at Cipriani,
probably.

06:45.579 --> 06:48.146
- And you drove back here
to the hotel?

06:51.976 --> 06:53.717
- I, uh...
[clears throat]

06:53.761 --> 06:56.111
I don't drive on game nights.

06:56.154 --> 06:57.460
We took the team bus
to dinner,

06:57.504 --> 06:59.593
and I walked back here
with Bronson.

07:01.725 --> 07:05.076
- And you never left the hotel
after returning to your suite?

07:05.120 --> 07:07.035
- The fire alarm went off
in the middle of the night.

07:07.078 --> 07:09.733
I went downstairs for that,
then back to bed.

07:09.777 --> 07:11.953
- On a Tuesday, Sonny can't
walk down the street

07:11.996 --> 07:13.128
without getting recognized.

07:13.171 --> 07:15.739
But during this comeback?

07:15.783 --> 07:18.133
If he'd left the hotel,
"TMZ" would've followed.

07:20.788 --> 07:23.834
- Mr. Langer, did you make
any phone calls last night?

07:23.878 --> 07:28.839
- I, uh, I called Bronson
a little before midnight.

07:28.883 --> 07:30.798
- Anyone else?

07:35.063 --> 07:38.022
[somber music]

07:38.066 --> 07:41.765
♪

07:41.809 --> 07:46.074
- [voice breaking]
I, uh, called Esme

07:46.117 --> 07:48.729
to say goodnight,
but she was already, uh--

07:59.827 --> 08:02.177
What, y'all think I did this?

08:02.220 --> 08:05.702
You think I took my children's
mother away from them?

08:05.746 --> 08:09.837
My family is my world.
I would never hurt them.

08:15.016 --> 08:19.542
- I need to ask
if your wife wore any jewelry.

08:19.586 --> 08:21.239
- Her wedding ring.

08:21.283 --> 08:25.548
She never took it off,
not even for Pilates.

08:25.592 --> 08:27.985
Why?
- It seems to be missing.

08:28.029 --> 08:29.639
Along with a few other items.

08:29.683 --> 08:31.641
- I don't care
about any of that.

08:31.685 --> 08:33.251
Just please find her ring.

08:33.295 --> 08:37.081
I got a 10-year-old daughter.
She gonna want it someday.

08:37.125 --> 08:38.692
A piece of her mom.

08:41.346 --> 08:42.739
- Daddy!
- Daddy!

08:42.783 --> 08:44.654
- Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

08:44.698 --> 08:47.831
Oh, this side, this side.
My arm.

08:47.875 --> 08:49.354
How you guys doing?

08:49.398 --> 08:51.008
You all right? Look at me.

08:51.052 --> 08:53.010
Everybody's gonna be okay,
all right?

08:53.054 --> 08:54.098
All right,
keep your head up, buddy.

08:54.142 --> 08:56.231
- Okay.
- We got this.

08:56.274 --> 08:59.016
- Did you have a prior working
relationship with Mrs. Langer?

08:59.060 --> 09:00.801
- Had I driven her before? No.

09:00.844 --> 09:04.108
But you know how every couple
gets a celebrity hall pass?

09:04.152 --> 09:07.851
- Esme was yours?
- She was my wife's.

09:07.895 --> 09:09.679
- Sorry about that.
How can I help you?

09:09.723 --> 09:11.855
- We need to confirm
a drop off from last night.

09:11.899 --> 09:13.248
Esme Langer?

09:15.946 --> 09:17.208
- Looks like
she was dropped off

09:17.252 --> 09:20.298
at her home address
in Greenwich at 12:14 a.m.

09:20.342 --> 09:23.606
- Did you notice anything
strange about Esme last night?

09:23.650 --> 09:25.869
- She was cool.
Her friend was a freak.

09:25.913 --> 09:27.088
- How so?

09:27.131 --> 09:29.046
- She was obsessed
with Esme or something.

09:29.090 --> 09:30.831
Kept pressuring her
to keep partying,

09:30.874 --> 09:32.659
wouldn't take no
for an answer.

09:32.702 --> 09:34.878
Mrs. Langer was pretty drunk
when I dropped her off.

09:34.922 --> 09:36.401
Wasn't my business to comment

09:36.445 --> 09:39.274
but, you know,
just something I noticed.

09:41.668 --> 09:43.887
- Sure, I can be
a little extra sometimes,

09:43.931 --> 09:47.630
but I just--I wanted
to cheer Esme up,

09:47.674 --> 09:49.893
help her let loose a little.

09:49.937 --> 09:51.678
Oh, my God.

09:51.721 --> 09:53.941
Crying on your birthday
really is bad luck.

09:56.291 --> 09:58.902
- Were she and Sonny
having problems?

09:58.946 --> 10:00.382
- No way.

10:00.425 --> 10:03.254
They were having this, like,
second honeymoon phase.

10:03.298 --> 10:04.734
When we got to her house,

10:04.778 --> 10:07.737
it looked like
a frickin' florist's.

10:07.781 --> 10:10.000
- And she wasn't upset
not to have him there?

10:10.044 --> 10:11.741
- She knew better
than anybody

10:11.785 --> 10:13.743
that birthdays
happen every year,

10:13.787 --> 10:15.919
but Sonny's big comeback?

10:15.963 --> 10:17.225
That's once in a lifetime.

10:17.268 --> 10:18.879
- Why wasn't she at his game?

10:18.922 --> 10:21.795
- Oh, she stopped going
to his games before he retired.

10:21.838 --> 10:23.971
It's that stupid
Kate Upton curse.

10:24.014 --> 10:26.930
- So you're saying fans were
blaming Esme for Sonny's slump?

10:26.974 --> 10:29.019
- For his slump,
for his retirement,

10:29.063 --> 10:31.152
every time he missed a layup.

10:31.195 --> 10:35.199
Sonny felt terrible about it,
but Esme, she was such a sport.

10:35.243 --> 10:37.027
She said that the seats
in their home theater

10:37.071 --> 10:39.377
were comfier
than courtside anyway.

10:41.162 --> 10:42.990
- And what upset
her last night?

10:43.033 --> 10:44.818
- She'd gotten
into this confrontation

10:44.861 --> 10:47.081
in the carpool line
yesterday morning.

10:47.124 --> 10:49.257
This creep was
taking pictures of her.

10:49.300 --> 10:51.781
- Doesn't paparazzi kinda
come with the territory?

10:51.825 --> 10:53.261
- Yeah, but this was different.

10:53.304 --> 10:56.090
It wasn't the first time
this guy had harassed her.

10:56.133 --> 10:58.222
And then he showed up
at her kid's school,

10:58.266 --> 11:00.660
and she was so freaked.

11:02.444 --> 11:04.185
- Esme has a stalker.

11:04.228 --> 11:06.796
She confronted him
yesterday morning.

11:06.840 --> 11:09.146
Her friend says
that she filmed it.

11:09.190 --> 11:12.497
Hana's looking into it. Ortiz?

11:12.541 --> 11:14.761
- Cipriani maître d'
and hotel cameras

11:14.804 --> 11:16.763
both confirm
what Sonny's agent told you.

11:16.806 --> 11:18.808
Sonny finished dinner
at 11:21 p.m.

11:18.852 --> 11:21.289
and took the elevator up to
his room seven minutes later,

11:21.332 --> 11:24.814
where he stayed until 2:02 a.m.
when the fire alarm went off.

11:24.858 --> 11:28.339
- To the delight of every
hotel guest with an iPhone.

11:28.383 --> 11:30.167
He and Esme own six cars.

11:30.211 --> 11:32.822
All of which were accounted for
at their Greenwich home.

11:32.866 --> 11:35.477
- His statements are clean.
No Ubers, no drivers.

11:35.520 --> 11:37.087
The only calls he made
were to his agent

11:37.131 --> 11:38.349
and Esme, just like he said.

11:38.393 --> 11:40.003
- And the ME put
Esme's time of death

11:40.047 --> 11:41.744
between 12:30 and 1:00.

11:43.877 --> 11:45.748
- So we're ruling Sonny out?

11:45.792 --> 11:48.185
- At least for now.

11:48.229 --> 11:49.752
- All right.
- Okay.

11:49.796 --> 11:51.841
The whole point of stealing
a sports star's memorabilia

11:51.885 --> 11:53.277
is to sell it, right?

11:53.321 --> 11:54.452
- Well, with all the coverage
the case is getting,

11:54.496 --> 11:57.194
the window to do that
is closing fast.

11:57.238 --> 11:59.893
- All right.
Let's look into pawn shops.

11:59.936 --> 12:01.938
- I found this
on Esme's iCloud.

12:01.982 --> 12:04.811
It was timestamped
from the morning of the murder.

12:06.508 --> 12:08.771
- How does it feel
to be hunted?

12:08.815 --> 12:11.034
Huh?
Do you like it?

12:11.078 --> 12:12.949
Show up
at my kids' school again,

12:12.993 --> 12:14.385
and I'm calling the police.

12:14.429 --> 12:16.039
- This goes on
for another 30 seconds,

12:16.083 --> 12:18.389
give or take a few F-bombs.

12:18.433 --> 12:19.869
- Can you isolate his face?

12:19.913 --> 12:22.959
- Well, he never turned around,
but I did get this--

12:23.003 --> 12:25.222
- It's a frontal shot,
at least.

12:25.266 --> 12:28.225
- His camera's in the way.
Won't work for facial rec.

12:28.269 --> 12:30.793
- Isobel, the kids
are doing just fine.

12:30.837 --> 12:33.796
- I am not here to babysit.
Just checking in.

12:33.840 --> 12:35.450
There's a lot of eyes
on this manhunt.

12:35.493 --> 12:36.930
We're getting pressure
to do this right,

12:36.973 --> 12:38.888
and speed has also
been emphasized.

12:38.932 --> 12:40.237
- A presser would help
with that.

12:40.281 --> 12:42.457
- Well, OPCA is not going
to approve a reward.

12:42.500 --> 12:43.980
- I'm not sure
we'd need one.

12:44.024 --> 12:46.809
Esme has 8.3 million
social media followers

12:46.853 --> 12:49.203
who want to help bring
her killer to justice for free.

12:49.246 --> 12:52.815
- We just need to ID that face.
Or partial face.

12:52.859 --> 12:54.817
- No other suspects?

12:54.861 --> 12:56.993
- He's the closest thing
we have.

12:57.037 --> 12:58.908
And without facial rec,
public interest

12:58.952 --> 13:01.476
is our only hope of IDing him.

13:01.519 --> 13:03.434
- So this stalker isn't
a formal suspect?

13:03.478 --> 13:05.088
- Nope.

13:05.132 --> 13:07.438
But whoever killed Esme knew
when she'd be home last night.

13:07.482 --> 13:09.092
- And that she'd be alone.

13:09.136 --> 13:10.441
- You sure you want
to go public

13:10.485 --> 13:12.139
with a person of interest?

13:12.182 --> 13:15.142
[suspenseful music]

13:15.185 --> 13:22.192
♪

13:23.367 --> 13:25.152
- Yeah. I'm sure.

13:28.285 --> 13:30.853
- A person of interest
wanted for questioning

13:30.897 --> 13:33.160
in the murder of Esme Langer.

13:33.203 --> 13:35.553
This subject is a white male,

13:35.597 --> 13:38.339
approximately 6 feet tall,
180 pounds,

13:38.382 --> 13:41.168
wearing dark pants
and a denim jacket.

13:41.211 --> 13:44.345
He has been seen
more than once in the vicinity

13:44.388 --> 13:46.913
of Saint Michael's Day School
in Greenwich.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.480
- Mike Short.
S-H-O-R-T.

13:49.524 --> 13:52.309
He's taller, though.
Maybe 6'3"?

13:52.353 --> 13:53.963
I'm telling you, it's him--

13:54.007 --> 13:56.052
- This individual is a person
of interest who we believe

13:56.096 --> 13:59.012
may have pertinent information
to a crime.

13:59.055 --> 14:01.144
Our investigation
is running around the clock

14:01.188 --> 14:03.581
and we will cont--

14:03.625 --> 14:05.409
- What are you doing?

14:05.453 --> 14:07.498
- It's you, isn't it?

14:07.542 --> 14:09.631
You only own
one ugly-ass jacket.

14:09.674 --> 14:12.025
- Hang up the phone.

14:12.068 --> 14:14.201
Hey, Mike.

14:14.244 --> 14:15.898
- Hey, what the--no!
No!

14:15.942 --> 14:19.075
[grunting]

14:19.119 --> 14:21.904
- Why did you that? Why?

14:24.298 --> 14:26.387
[roars]

14:26.430 --> 14:33.263
♪

14:42.142 --> 14:43.491
- Hey, Barnes.

14:43.534 --> 14:46.537
I think I got something
on the tip line.

14:46.581 --> 14:47.712
- It's you, isn't it?

14:47.756 --> 14:49.018
You only own
one ugly-ass jacket.

14:49.062 --> 14:51.847
- Hang up the phone.
- What the--no! No!

14:51.891 --> 14:54.458
- Caller ID's himself
as Aaron Roe.

14:54.502 --> 14:56.983
Says Esme's stalker
is his roommate, Mike Short.

15:01.683 --> 15:03.772
- Yeah, he's got
a criminal record.

15:03.815 --> 15:05.556
An arrest and conviction
for possession

15:05.600 --> 15:06.906
of child pornography.

15:06.949 --> 15:09.082
He's a registered
sex offender on parole.

15:09.125 --> 15:12.085
[suspenseful music]

15:12.128 --> 15:16.045
♪

15:16.089 --> 15:18.569
[knock at door]

15:18.613 --> 15:21.921
- Mr. Roe? Mr. Short?
This is the FBI.

15:26.099 --> 15:28.449
- We got a body
on the floor in here.

15:42.506 --> 15:44.073
- Kitchen's clear.

15:44.117 --> 15:51.124
♪

15:59.306 --> 16:00.829
- That's a suicide.

16:05.094 --> 16:08.924
- It's him.
That's Esme's stalker.

16:08.968 --> 16:10.273
- When he caught Aaron
turning him in,

16:10.317 --> 16:11.492
he knew he'd go down for being

16:11.535 --> 16:13.233
too close
to an elementary school.

16:13.276 --> 16:15.191
The only thing worse than death
for a pedophile

16:15.235 --> 16:18.064
is the prospect of prison.

16:18.107 --> 16:19.979
- Hence the murder-suicide.

16:23.547 --> 16:25.245
- It's not your fault, Jess.

16:31.164 --> 16:33.862
- No jerseys or trophies,
but I got this.

16:33.905 --> 16:35.211
Wedding ring.

16:35.255 --> 16:38.127
Man came in this morning,
wanted 25 grand for it.

16:38.171 --> 16:41.000
- A cut like this is worth
more like a 100,000.

16:41.043 --> 16:44.264
- Tiffany's is across town.
Best I could do was 10k.

16:45.874 --> 16:47.049
I can describe the guy.

16:47.093 --> 16:49.747
- That's great,
but we'll need a photo.

16:49.791 --> 16:51.836
- Surveillance cameras
are bad for business.

16:51.880 --> 16:53.142
I'm not required to have any.

16:53.186 --> 16:54.578
- No, but you are required

16:54.622 --> 16:56.276
to submit
sworn transaction statements

16:56.319 --> 16:58.234
to the licensing authority
in Connecticut.

16:58.278 --> 16:59.801
You're doing that,
though, right?

16:59.844 --> 17:00.889
- Every week.

17:00.932 --> 17:01.933
- Then you wouldn't mind
showing us

17:01.977 --> 17:03.152
those statements, right?

17:03.196 --> 17:05.981
- You got a warrant?
- We could get one.

17:09.593 --> 17:12.727
- I mean, let's just run this
serial number through NCIC.

17:12.770 --> 17:15.164
I mean, I'm sure a law-abiding
citizen like Mr. Troglio here

17:15.208 --> 17:17.036
wouldn't be purchasing
stolen property.

17:21.866 --> 17:23.738
Well, would you look at that?

17:30.092 --> 17:32.051
- You want talk about it?

17:32.094 --> 17:34.879
- No.

17:34.923 --> 17:37.839
How's your daughter?
Ingrid, right?

17:37.882 --> 17:40.146
- You really want to know?
- Yeah.

17:40.189 --> 17:43.062
It's better than thinking
about what we just saw.

17:43.105 --> 17:45.716
- She's--she's really good,
actually.

17:45.760 --> 17:47.240
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

17:47.283 --> 17:49.633
She's happy to be around
her brother and her dad again.

17:49.677 --> 17:51.983
So it's nice feeling
like a family again.

17:52.027 --> 17:53.594
- But?

17:53.637 --> 17:55.770
- You know, I always thought
my ex and I were better apart,

17:55.813 --> 17:58.207
but I got to admit, it's nice
having him to talk to again.

17:58.251 --> 18:00.688
Just don't want to get
the kids' hopes up, you know?

18:00.731 --> 18:02.124
So it's complicated.

18:02.168 --> 18:03.734
- Families always are.

18:03.778 --> 18:05.301
[phone rings]

18:05.345 --> 18:07.042
Hey, Hana. What's up?

18:07.086 --> 18:09.914
- Our North American
pawn tour was a success.

18:09.958 --> 18:11.220
Esme's wedding ring was sold.

18:11.264 --> 18:12.743
We ran facial rec
on the seller,

18:12.787 --> 18:14.745
and his name's Douglas Jones.

18:14.789 --> 18:16.747
Sending you his photo
and his last known now.

18:16.791 --> 18:18.184
- Douglas Jones.

18:18.227 --> 18:21.100
- He lives in Darien.
You want PD dispatched?

18:21.143 --> 18:22.144
- Yeah, request units,

18:22.188 --> 18:24.015
but tell 'em
to sit a block over.

18:24.059 --> 18:25.756
With the attention
this case has gotten,

18:25.800 --> 18:27.018
he's going to be on high alert.

18:27.062 --> 18:29.282
Uniforms might spook him.

18:29.325 --> 18:32.111
[tense music]

18:32.154 --> 18:34.330
♪

18:34.374 --> 18:35.984
- FBI. Stop!

18:36.027 --> 18:37.855
- I'm heading out the back.

18:37.899 --> 18:38.987
- He's heading east.

18:49.693 --> 18:51.695
- That's him.
- What I do?

18:51.739 --> 18:53.088
- You're gonna have
a life sentence

18:53.132 --> 18:54.263
to figure it out in prison.

18:54.307 --> 18:55.786
- A life sentence for what?

18:55.830 --> 18:57.136
- What do you think?

18:57.179 --> 19:02.184
♪

19:02.228 --> 19:04.360
- I didn't kill that lady.
- You severed her head.

19:04.404 --> 19:07.972
- I didn't. Last night, okay?

19:08.016 --> 19:09.235
I get a call to take a knife

19:09.278 --> 19:10.366
and a bunch of basketball stuff

19:10.410 --> 19:11.889
out of this big house
in Greenwich.

19:11.933 --> 19:13.543
Told me to wipe down
the door handles

19:13.587 --> 19:16.111
and take the diamond ring off
the woman's finger as payment.

19:17.765 --> 19:22.944
I didn't kill anybody.
I'm just a cleaner--a fixer.

19:22.987 --> 19:24.902
- A fixer for who?

19:24.946 --> 19:27.166
- Look, man, you can give us
a name in the next two seconds,

19:27.209 --> 19:28.993
or you can go away
for grand theft and murder.

19:29.037 --> 19:30.386
And not in that order.

19:32.519 --> 19:34.216
- I want a lawyer.

19:38.089 --> 19:39.917
- We have got a murder suspect

19:39.961 --> 19:41.832
in possession
of a murder weapon.

19:41.876 --> 19:44.705
- Doug had no idea we tracked
him down through Esme's ring.

19:44.748 --> 19:47.011
Invoking that puts him
at the scene of the crime.

19:47.055 --> 19:48.448
The only people who do that
are the innocent.

19:48.491 --> 19:50.232
- Or the stupid.

19:50.276 --> 19:52.103
In 20 years,
I have never worked a case

19:52.147 --> 19:53.714
with this much public interest.

19:53.757 --> 19:55.194
We've gotta get the press off
our backs

19:55.237 --> 19:56.891
before this thing
spins out of control.

19:56.934 --> 19:58.066
They know we've got
a guy in custody,

19:58.109 --> 20:00.286
and OPCA
is ready to release a name.

20:05.029 --> 20:07.206
- We can't.
Not until we're sure.

20:07.249 --> 20:09.208
- Is this about Aaron Roe
and Mike Short?

20:11.514 --> 20:14.169
Jess, you made the best call
you could

20:14.213 --> 20:15.736
with the information you had.

20:15.779 --> 20:17.738
That's the job.

20:17.781 --> 20:19.305
Their deaths aren't on you.

20:21.176 --> 20:23.004
- Just give me and my team
a few more days.

20:23.047 --> 20:24.266
I know murderers.

20:24.310 --> 20:27.008
Something's telling me
that Doug isn't one.

20:27.051 --> 20:28.270
- 24 hours.

20:28.314 --> 20:29.750
And then I'm holding
a press conference

20:29.793 --> 20:32.405
announcing Doug Jones
as the FBI's primary suspect.

20:32.448 --> 20:37.758
♪

20:41.718 --> 20:42.893
- Let's say Doug's
telling the truth.

20:42.937 --> 20:44.286
- That someone paid him

20:44.330 --> 20:45.592
to clean up
the scene of Esme's murder?

20:45.635 --> 20:47.724
- Yes--it'd have to be
someone with connections,

20:47.768 --> 20:49.509
someone in the know enough
to have a fixer.

20:49.552 --> 20:51.728
- Is there anything
in the phone record?

20:51.772 --> 20:53.382
- He didn't make or receive
any calls

20:53.426 --> 20:54.731
on the night of the murder
except for this one,

20:54.775 --> 20:56.429
at 12:32 a.m.

20:56.472 --> 20:59.432
It's unlisted, but I traced it
to a T2 Enterprises.

20:59.475 --> 21:01.564
It's a shell company,
so the trail goes cold.

21:01.608 --> 21:03.392
- You know, anybody who doubted
his comeback,

21:03.436 --> 21:04.741
he proved 'em wrong.

21:04.785 --> 21:06.743
Scored 28 points
in the final quarter.

21:06.787 --> 21:09.572
- So Sonny played
till the buzzer sounded

21:09.616 --> 21:11.095
on an injured shoulder?

21:11.139 --> 21:13.924
- Well, his body had been
on ice for four years.

21:13.968 --> 21:16.797
- But during the game,
Sonny didn't hurt his shoulder?

21:19.060 --> 21:21.715
- No.

21:21.758 --> 21:25.327
- Then how'd he get injured?

21:25.371 --> 21:27.024
- You able to find
Esme's sister yet?

21:27.068 --> 21:29.853
- Yeah, she's in White Plains.
Her name's Mindy.

21:29.897 --> 21:31.420
- Let's see
if she knows anything.

21:31.464 --> 21:33.335
[suspenseful music]

21:33.379 --> 21:36.120
- Just watch the movie, guys,
and I'll be right out here.

21:36.164 --> 21:38.558
Let me know
if you need anything.

21:38.601 --> 21:40.299
Sorry.

21:40.342 --> 21:42.823
Sonny asked me to keep the kids
here until the press dies down.

21:42.866 --> 21:44.955
They don't like letting me
out of their sight.

21:44.999 --> 21:46.696
- We understand.

21:46.740 --> 21:49.960
- Can you tell us
about Esme and Sonny?

21:50.004 --> 21:52.441
- Their marriage had
its ups and downs.

21:52.485 --> 21:55.792
More downs than ups,
especially after Sonny retired.

21:55.836 --> 21:57.141
- That's right
when your sister's career

21:57.185 --> 21:58.534
really kicked off.

21:58.578 --> 21:59.796
Was Sonny ever jealous?

21:59.840 --> 22:01.145
- I don't know.

22:01.189 --> 22:03.583
He'd gone inward
the last few years,

22:03.626 --> 22:06.455
spending less time at home,
more nights in the city.

22:06.499 --> 22:09.806
Esme said when she'd pressed
him about it, he lashed out.

22:09.850 --> 22:10.981
- Physically?

22:11.025 --> 22:12.983
- He never hit her,

22:13.027 --> 22:14.855
but he developed a temper.

22:14.898 --> 22:17.466
- Developed. So this was new?

22:17.510 --> 22:19.773
- They have this saying
in pro ball,

22:19.816 --> 22:21.949
"Every athlete dies twice.

22:21.992 --> 22:24.560
"Once when he takes
his last breath,

22:24.604 --> 22:26.649
and once when he retires."

22:26.693 --> 22:28.608
- So was Esme hopeful
their marriage would improve

22:28.651 --> 22:29.783
when he returned
to basketball?

22:29.826 --> 22:31.393
- It already did.

22:31.437 --> 22:34.570
The day he started training
for his comeback last summer?

22:34.614 --> 22:38.618
Esme christened it
their new anniversary date.

22:38.661 --> 22:40.968
- So Sonny was a new man?
- Completely.

22:41.011 --> 22:42.970
Every day was
a new bouquet of roses

22:43.013 --> 22:44.798
or piece of jewelry.

22:44.841 --> 22:47.975
Esme didn't wear any of it,
of course, but still--

22:48.018 --> 22:49.150
- What do you mean?

22:49.193 --> 22:51.413
- She stopped wearing
jewelry years ago.

22:51.457 --> 22:54.851
- Even her wedding ring?
- Especially that.

22:54.895 --> 22:56.462
Kim Kardashian was a friend.

22:56.505 --> 22:58.899
Her Paris robbery
gave Esme a wake-up call.

22:58.942 --> 23:01.902
She started keeping all her
jewelry in her bedroom safe.

23:01.945 --> 23:08.952
♪

23:09.997 --> 23:11.215
- Hana just spoke with Becca.

23:11.259 --> 23:12.739
She confirmed that Esme was not

23:12.782 --> 23:14.741
wearing her wedding ring
the night of her birthday.

23:14.784 --> 23:16.482
- Then how did Doug steal
the wedding ring off her finger

23:16.525 --> 23:17.657
a few hours later?

23:17.700 --> 23:19.441
- Someone put it there
for him to find.

23:19.485 --> 23:21.095
- Just because Sonny has access
to the safe

23:21.138 --> 23:22.705
doesn't mean he killed Esme.

23:22.749 --> 23:25.186
- When we spoke, Sonny said
Esme wore her ring every day.

23:25.229 --> 23:26.448
Why would he lie about that?

23:26.492 --> 23:27.928
Why force us to track down
a ring

23:27.971 --> 23:29.669
that he knew Esme never wore?

23:29.712 --> 23:31.453
- Maybe he was framing Doug.

23:31.497 --> 23:34.761
- Okay, so he kills her,
calls Doug to clean the scene

23:34.804 --> 23:36.197
making it look like a robbery.

23:36.240 --> 23:37.981
Tells him to take
the ring as payment

23:38.025 --> 23:39.853
knowing that he'd pawn it
and we would track it down.

23:39.896 --> 23:41.071
Is that what you're saying?

23:41.115 --> 23:42.551
- I reviewed the security
footage myself.

23:42.595 --> 23:46.120
Sonny didn't leave the hotel
after 11:28 that night.

23:46.163 --> 23:47.817
Hang on a second.

23:51.125 --> 23:52.822
- Ritz-Carlton,
how may I help you?

23:52.866 --> 23:54.084
- Yes, hello.

23:54.128 --> 23:56.696
I'm calling on behalf
of Alixe Al Swaidi.

23:56.739 --> 23:59.046
She's a frequent guest of
your Imperial Suite in Paris.

23:59.089 --> 24:01.265
She'll be stateside shortly,
and her security detail

24:01.309 --> 24:03.572
needs to confirm that you have
a Streisand entrance

24:03.616 --> 24:05.618
at your location for privacy.

24:05.661 --> 24:07.228
- Yes, of course.

24:07.271 --> 24:08.577
- And there are no cameras
at that exit.

24:08.621 --> 24:09.839
Is that correct?

24:09.883 --> 24:11.754
- Well, I'm really not
supposed to say.

24:11.798 --> 24:13.713
- Can I take that as a yes?

24:13.756 --> 24:16.106
- Discretion for our VIPs
is paramount.

24:16.150 --> 24:18.195
- Thank you.
I'll let Ms. Al Swaidi know.

24:18.239 --> 24:19.762
- Streisand entrance?

24:19.806 --> 24:21.242
Yeah, you live in Miami
long enough,

24:21.285 --> 24:22.896
you pick up the lingo.

24:22.939 --> 24:24.245
The point is--

24:24.288 --> 24:25.899
- Sonny could've come and gone
through that exit

24:25.942 --> 24:28.292
any time of the night,
undetected.

24:28.336 --> 24:29.946
- That's right.

24:29.990 --> 24:32.775
- But does the timeline work?

24:32.819 --> 24:34.777
- Well, he would've had
to break some traffic laws,

24:34.821 --> 24:36.083
but feasibly, yeah.

24:36.126 --> 24:37.693
He could've gone to Connecticut
to kill Esme

24:37.737 --> 24:40.000
and then gotten back
to his hotel by 2:00 a.m.,

24:40.043 --> 24:41.088
which is when
the fire alarm went off.

24:41.131 --> 24:42.785
- The fire alarm
wasn't a fluke.

24:42.829 --> 24:45.571
Sonny pulled it.
He's building an alibi.

24:45.614 --> 24:47.616
- Jess, are we sure?

24:47.660 --> 24:49.139
What if we're wrong?

24:49.183 --> 24:53.100
♪

24:53.143 --> 24:56.320
- Truffle fries,
your favorite.

24:56.364 --> 24:57.539
Try one.

24:57.583 --> 25:00.107
- Nah, man. I can't.

25:00.150 --> 25:01.674
- You need to keep
your strength up.

25:01.717 --> 25:03.806
- Hey, man, stop.

25:03.850 --> 25:06.809
Can you stop managing me
for one minute?

25:06.853 --> 25:09.203
Are you my agent
or are you my friend?

25:09.246 --> 25:13.294
- I'm both.

25:13.337 --> 25:15.078
Sonny.

25:15.122 --> 25:17.864
Look at me.

25:17.907 --> 25:19.866
Do you understand?
I'm just trying to help you.

25:19.909 --> 25:21.258
- "Help" me?

25:22.608 --> 25:24.566
Help me?
You trying to help me?

25:24.610 --> 25:25.828
You made that promise already.

25:25.872 --> 25:26.829
But you lied.
- I can't breathe.

25:26.873 --> 25:28.048
- You lied.
- Sonny, please--

25:28.091 --> 25:30.833
- Remember?
You said you would help me?

25:30.877 --> 25:33.880
Esme dead. She gone.
- [choking]

25:37.710 --> 25:39.320
- Copy that, sir.

25:39.363 --> 25:42.323
[suspenseful music]

25:42.366 --> 25:46.283
♪

25:46.327 --> 25:47.807
- What happened?

25:47.850 --> 25:50.374
- Room service came to pick up
a tray a half-hour ago.

25:50.418 --> 25:52.202
Found him strangled to death.

25:52.246 --> 25:53.682
- And Sonny Langer?

25:53.726 --> 25:55.684
- There's no sign of him
in here or on surveillance.

25:55.728 --> 25:57.381
- Okay.
Thank you, Detective.

25:57.425 --> 25:58.426
- This doesn't make sense.

25:58.469 --> 26:00.602
Sonny didn't know
we were onto him.

26:00.646 --> 26:02.386
If he thought he got away
with killing Esme--

26:02.430 --> 26:03.866
- Then why kill
Bronson and flee?

26:03.910 --> 26:06.216
[phone buzzes]

26:06.260 --> 26:08.436
Jess wants us back.
Kristin found something.

26:11.221 --> 26:12.571
- Street camera
a block from the Ritz

26:12.614 --> 26:13.702
picked up Sonny leaving

26:13.746 --> 26:15.835
in Bronson's G-Wagon
45 minutes ago.

26:15.878 --> 26:18.315
- Plates are logged and PD's
ready to go,

26:18.359 --> 26:21.536
but we need to know
which direction to point them.

26:21.580 --> 26:22.885
Kristin, you want to show them?

26:22.929 --> 26:24.365
- Yeah, so last week,

26:24.408 --> 26:26.410
Sonny filmed an exclusive
interview with Meryl Marks.

26:26.454 --> 26:28.848
It was set to air straight
after his first game back,

26:28.891 --> 26:30.806
but it was preempted
by the hurricane coverage.

26:34.375 --> 26:37.421
- You know, you shocked
a lot of people

26:37.465 --> 26:39.685
when you retired
with no explanation.

26:39.728 --> 26:42.426
Do you feel like you
owe your fans one now?

26:42.470 --> 26:44.472
- Meryl, I'm an athlete.

26:44.515 --> 26:48.432
And people sometimes
think you're invincible.

26:48.476 --> 26:50.609
But I'm human. Humans suffer.

26:50.652 --> 26:52.698
And I know I did
when I was retired.

26:52.741 --> 26:55.439
Headaches, memory loss,
mood swings,

26:55.483 --> 26:57.224
difficulty concentrating,
you name it.

26:57.267 --> 27:00.706
- Are you talking about CTE?
- Yes.

27:00.749 --> 27:03.273
I got my first concussion
in high school.

27:03.317 --> 27:05.711
Three in college and who knows
how many in the pros.

27:05.754 --> 27:06.842
They compound.

27:06.886 --> 27:08.757
If your brain hasn't healed

27:08.801 --> 27:10.150
before that next hit...

27:10.193 --> 27:17.200
♪

27:18.767 --> 27:20.900
That's me
a month before I retired.

27:20.943 --> 27:24.164
- You know, the public has
never heard of any of this.

27:24.207 --> 27:25.644
- That's because
I thought bravery

27:25.687 --> 27:27.384
meant hiding your weaknesses.

27:27.428 --> 27:29.212
Now I know that if
you ask for help,

27:29.256 --> 27:31.301
that's the bravest thing
a person can do.

27:31.345 --> 27:34.740
- So, are you talking therapy?
Medication?

27:34.783 --> 27:37.307
- Yes, and something
called CHEVAL.

27:37.351 --> 27:39.962
It's a rotating chair
that's designed

27:40.006 --> 27:43.792
to forge new neural pathways
in your brain, and it works.

27:43.836 --> 27:46.403
- So you're saying,
this new medical device

27:46.447 --> 27:49.842
actually improved
your symptoms?

27:49.885 --> 27:53.541
- The old Sonny,
he loved playing basketball.

27:53.584 --> 27:55.456
He loved life.
He loved his family.

27:55.499 --> 27:57.980
For the first time
that I can remember,

27:58.024 --> 28:00.940
I feel like him again.

28:00.983 --> 28:03.594
- CTE can't be diagnosed
for sure without an autopsy,

28:03.638 --> 28:05.945
but if he really has it,
this changes everything.

28:05.988 --> 28:07.555
- What are you, an expert?

28:07.598 --> 28:08.991
- I used to be a boxer.

28:09.035 --> 28:11.515
You have to educate yourself
on traumatic brain injury

28:11.559 --> 28:13.561
when you're getting hit
in the head every weekend.

28:13.604 --> 28:16.390
My point is,
with post-concussive syndrome,

28:16.433 --> 28:18.522
Sonny might not have control
of his own brain.

28:18.566 --> 28:20.394
He may have killed Esme
in a fit of rage,

28:20.437 --> 28:22.831
not some premeditated plan.

28:22.875 --> 28:24.964
- That would explain
his genuine show of grief

28:25.007 --> 28:26.574
when we spoke to him.

28:32.841 --> 28:36.366
- Looks like CHEVAL is patented
by a medical manufacturer

28:36.410 --> 28:38.325
called Essedarius.

28:38.368 --> 28:39.892
The machine works by activating

28:39.935 --> 28:42.851
the vestibular system
with peripheral stimulus.

28:42.895 --> 28:44.984
Other people say there's
no proof that it works at all.

28:45.027 --> 28:46.550
It's not FDA approved.

28:46.594 --> 28:49.379
- Guess who sat
on Essedarius' board?

28:49.423 --> 28:52.861
Bronson Styles--Sonny's agent.

28:52.905 --> 28:55.342
- So Bronson convinced Sonny
that Essedarius

28:55.385 --> 28:56.865
could cure him of CTE.

28:56.909 --> 28:59.781
He probably talked him
into making his comeback too.

28:59.825 --> 29:01.565
- Bronson didn't seem to care.

29:01.609 --> 29:03.480
As Sonny's agent
and as a board member,

29:03.524 --> 29:04.873
he stood to make millions.

29:04.917 --> 29:06.745
- So knowing Sonny's
mental deficits,

29:06.788 --> 29:08.572
Bronson tells Sonny he's cured.

29:08.616 --> 29:10.052
- And Sonny believes him.

29:10.096 --> 29:12.489
Thinks it's safe
to finally return to his family

29:12.533 --> 29:13.882
without the risk
of harming them.

29:13.926 --> 29:15.492
And it's only when
he kills Esme

29:15.536 --> 29:18.495
that he realizes
Bronson duped him.

29:18.539 --> 29:21.281
He kills him for it.

29:21.324 --> 29:23.805
- Who else is
on Essedarius' board?

29:23.849 --> 29:26.895
♪

29:26.939 --> 29:29.637
- Its founder is Nash Toledo,

29:29.680 --> 29:31.726
the billionaire entrepreneur
from Brooklyn.

29:31.770 --> 29:34.642
- A billionaire
with a few shell companies?

29:34.685 --> 29:36.557
- T2 Enterprises.

29:36.600 --> 29:38.733
The shell corp that called
Doug Jones

29:38.777 --> 29:40.300
the night of Esme's murder.

29:40.343 --> 29:41.867
- Any calls from Bronson
to Nash

29:41.910 --> 29:44.347
the night of the murder?

29:44.391 --> 29:46.436
- Yep--three minutes
before Nash called Doug.

29:46.480 --> 29:49.700
- Nash and Bronson
covered up Esme's murder

29:49.744 --> 29:53.095
to protect their company.
Bronson is dead.

29:53.139 --> 29:55.097
That would suggest
that Nash could be next.

29:55.141 --> 29:56.664
- Yeah, logically, it tracks,

29:56.707 --> 29:58.884
but Sonny's brain
isn't operating logically.

29:58.927 --> 30:00.450
It's the people closest to him

30:00.494 --> 30:01.843
that are flipping him
into a rage.

30:01.887 --> 30:04.672
Right? It's his wife.
It's Bronson.

30:06.848 --> 30:10.634
My gut says his next move
involves his kids.

30:10.678 --> 30:13.376
- Then let's trust your gut.
I'll go with you.

30:13.420 --> 30:15.770
I want everyone else
to Nash's place, bases covered.

30:15.814 --> 30:16.815
Let's move.

30:19.861 --> 30:21.776
- My technology saved Sonny.

30:21.820 --> 30:23.082
He should be
sending me flowers.

30:23.125 --> 30:24.648
- Have you talked
to Sonny recently?

30:24.692 --> 30:26.520
- I don't liaise with talent.

30:26.563 --> 30:28.957
- How about his agent,
Bronson Styles?

30:29.001 --> 30:30.654
He sits on the board
for Essedarius.

30:30.698 --> 30:34.354
- I can barely keep track
of my business partners,

30:34.397 --> 30:36.573
much less every board member.

30:36.617 --> 30:38.401
There's only so many hours
in the day.

30:38.445 --> 30:39.881
It's extraordinarily
difficult to manage--

30:39.925 --> 30:41.491
- Yeah, I don't know how you
summon up the willpower

30:41.535 --> 30:43.406
to just keep on going.

30:43.450 --> 30:44.712
Ballpark it.

30:44.755 --> 30:51.719
♪

30:51.762 --> 30:54.026
- Bronson and I talk
about every month or so.

30:54.069 --> 30:56.724
It's been at least that long
since we spoke.

30:56.767 --> 30:58.073
As I said, busy--

30:58.117 --> 30:59.901
- Aside from the call
that Bronson made to you

30:59.945 --> 31:03.731
at 12:29 a.m. on the night
of Esme Langer's murder, right?

31:03.774 --> 31:05.515
- And how about the call
you made to Doug Jones

31:05.559 --> 31:07.909
three minutes later?

31:07.953 --> 31:10.085
- Not ideal for business
when your star spokesman

31:10.129 --> 31:11.565
goes on a killing spree

31:11.608 --> 31:14.873
24 hours before your product
is set to launch, is it?

31:14.916 --> 31:16.091
- Sonny is sick.

31:16.135 --> 31:18.137
Your so-called technology
didn't help him.

31:18.180 --> 31:20.139
You just used him to line
your pockets.

31:20.182 --> 31:22.010
- And you helped
cover up the crime.

31:22.054 --> 31:24.143
That's accessory
after the fact to murder.

31:24.186 --> 31:25.796
- Take your hands off me.

31:25.840 --> 31:28.582
- Put your hands
behind your back.

31:31.715 --> 31:33.717
- I can't imagine billionaires
fare well in prison,

31:33.761 --> 31:34.980
but do keep us posted.

31:35.023 --> 31:36.720
- Let's go.

31:36.764 --> 31:38.070
[knocking at door]

31:41.203 --> 31:43.553
- Agent LaCroix.
What's going on?

31:43.597 --> 31:45.033
- We believe Sonny
murdered your sister.

31:45.077 --> 31:46.469
- What?

31:46.513 --> 31:48.167
- We need to get you
and the kids to a safe place.

31:48.210 --> 31:49.646
- He killed his agent tonight,

31:49.690 --> 31:50.952
and we think
he's coming here next.

31:50.996 --> 31:52.562
- He already did.
- When?

31:52.606 --> 31:54.564
- 15 minutes ago.
He seemed normal.

31:54.608 --> 31:55.826
Everything seemed fine.

31:55.870 --> 31:58.568
- Mindy, where are the kids?

31:58.612 --> 31:59.961
- He took them with him.

32:05.314 --> 32:06.663
- He's not at Nash's.

32:06.707 --> 32:08.622
- He's not at the hotel
or the Greenwich house.

32:08.665 --> 32:10.145
- If he was gonna hurt
the kids,

32:10.189 --> 32:11.407
I doubt
he'd bring 'em back here.

32:11.451 --> 32:13.714
- Oh, my God.
You think he'd do that?

32:13.757 --> 32:15.368
- We need you to focus.

32:15.411 --> 32:18.153
Did he say why he was taking
Haley and Frankie?

32:18.197 --> 32:20.112
- He said they were
going to have some fun.

32:20.155 --> 32:22.636
To get their minds off
of things.

32:22.679 --> 32:23.854
- Listen. You gotta think.

32:23.898 --> 32:25.769
- All he said was,
"We're going to the city

32:25.813 --> 32:27.771
to have some fun."

32:27.815 --> 32:29.338
- Could you get me
your phone, please?

32:29.382 --> 32:33.299
[suspenseful music]

32:33.342 --> 32:34.561
- I took you here once.
Remember?

32:34.604 --> 32:36.650
- With Mommy?
- That's right. With Mommy.

32:36.693 --> 32:38.478
- Why are we even
going this way?

32:38.521 --> 32:40.306
- Oh, it's bigtime now,
baby girl.

32:40.349 --> 32:42.699
This is the superstar entrance.

32:42.743 --> 32:45.485
Wait, y'all hear that?

32:45.528 --> 32:47.095
- I don't hear anything.

32:47.139 --> 32:50.098
- That's right.
No press, no fans.

32:50.142 --> 32:51.404
Just you.

32:51.447 --> 32:54.450
[phone ringing]

32:57.366 --> 32:58.715
Mindy, this isn't a good time--

32:58.759 --> 33:01.457
- Sonny, this is Jess LaCroix
with the FBI.

33:01.501 --> 33:02.545
- Leave me alone.

33:02.589 --> 33:03.807
- Sonny, wait,
please hear us out.

33:03.851 --> 33:05.548
It's about your kids.

33:08.551 --> 33:10.466
- You guys go up ahead, okay?
I'll be right there.

33:10.510 --> 33:11.728
- Okay.

33:13.817 --> 33:15.297
- What do you want?

33:15.341 --> 33:17.560
- My name's Kristin.
We met at the Ritz.

33:17.604 --> 33:19.475
Do you remember me?

33:19.519 --> 33:21.347
- I think so.

33:21.390 --> 33:25.351
I don't, um--I don't--
the edges are all fuzzy.

33:25.394 --> 33:27.701
- That's all right, Sonny.
That's okay.

33:27.744 --> 33:29.355
We just want to help you.

33:29.398 --> 33:30.573
- You can't.

33:30.617 --> 33:31.792
- I know a lot
of people have tried,

33:31.835 --> 33:34.186
and I know a lot of people
have let you down.

33:34.229 --> 33:36.101
I don't want to be
one of those people.

33:36.144 --> 33:42.237
♪

33:42.281 --> 33:44.065
Sonny, I want you
to help me help you.

33:44.109 --> 33:45.327
- How?

33:45.371 --> 33:47.199
- By coming up
with a game plan, together.

33:47.242 --> 33:49.853
- What--what game plan?
- I don't know, you tell me.

33:49.897 --> 33:53.248
What do you want?
Where do you want to go?

33:55.468 --> 33:57.165
- What do you want, Sonny?

34:00.429 --> 34:03.693
- I want Esme back.

34:03.737 --> 34:05.739
I loved her so much.

34:05.782 --> 34:09.090
I want my kids to know
that I loved her.

34:09.134 --> 34:10.918
I want them to know
that I'm sorry.

34:10.961 --> 34:13.703
How sorry I am.
I want to be happy again.

34:13.747 --> 34:15.140
- We understand, Sonny.

34:15.183 --> 34:17.229
Your career
robbed you of a life--

34:17.272 --> 34:21.363
- You're wrong.
Basketball gave me my life.

34:21.407 --> 34:22.712
At the beginning,

34:22.756 --> 34:24.845
it was the only place
that I ever felt happy.

34:24.888 --> 34:26.716
- Do it! Take the shot!

34:26.760 --> 34:28.240
- [laughs]

34:28.283 --> 34:30.242
- Go for it!

34:30.285 --> 34:31.808
- It gave me everything.

34:33.854 --> 34:36.117
- He's not going
to the Garden--he's going back

34:36.161 --> 34:38.206
to the last place
he loved playing the game.

34:38.250 --> 34:39.773
His college court at Hudson.

34:39.816 --> 34:41.688
- Okay. Where's that?

34:41.731 --> 34:43.429
- Check a left
at the next light.

34:43.472 --> 34:45.779
The FDR'll be faster.

34:45.822 --> 34:52.220
♪

34:52.264 --> 34:55.702
- Conference championship,
22 seconds left, down by two.

34:55.745 --> 34:57.269
I think that's it.

34:57.312 --> 35:00.750
Right? I'm out of options.
But what does Daddy always say?

35:00.794 --> 35:01.882
- Pressure is a privilege.

35:01.925 --> 35:03.449
- That's right.

35:03.492 --> 35:04.624
Now, Donny and I

35:04.667 --> 35:05.799
trained for this
every day in practice,

35:05.842 --> 35:07.366
so he knows exactly
where I'ma be.

35:07.409 --> 35:09.716
So he passes.
And that's when I get my shot.

35:11.674 --> 35:14.416
- Haley. What's wrong?

35:16.592 --> 35:18.420
- Sonny--
- Come on. Come here.

35:18.464 --> 35:20.727
- Can we talk to you?

35:20.770 --> 35:23.295
- Stand down.
Everybody, stand down.

35:23.338 --> 35:25.210
Stand down.

35:25.253 --> 35:27.168
- Daddy, I'm scared.
- It's okay. It's okay.

35:27.212 --> 35:28.561
- Why do you have a gun?
- It's okay.

35:28.604 --> 35:30.302
It's okay. Everything's okay.

35:30.345 --> 35:33.174
- Sonny, why don't we try
to make this easy?

35:36.351 --> 35:37.874
Why don't we let the kids go?

35:40.399 --> 35:41.661
- No.

35:41.704 --> 35:44.229
It's okay, it's okay.
I gotta protect them.

35:44.272 --> 35:45.621
I gotta protect them.

35:45.665 --> 35:48.276
No one's gonna protect them.
No one protected me.

35:48.320 --> 35:50.887
- We know you want to keep
Haley and Frankie safe, Sonny.

35:50.931 --> 35:52.846
We know.

35:52.889 --> 35:55.588
The only way to do that
is to let them go.

35:57.546 --> 36:00.897
- I can't.
- Yes, you can.

36:00.941 --> 36:04.249
You can.
You did once before, right?

36:04.292 --> 36:05.598
You knew you were sick,

36:05.641 --> 36:07.121
you were afraid
you'd hurt them.

36:07.165 --> 36:10.864
So you protected them, right?
Protect them from pain.

36:10.907 --> 36:12.561
- Come on,
they don't know that.

36:12.605 --> 36:14.911
They ain't gonna believe me.

36:14.955 --> 36:16.478
- They will.

36:18.872 --> 36:20.787
- And if you let them go,

36:20.830 --> 36:24.356
we'll make sure they do.
I promise.

36:24.399 --> 36:31.276
♪

36:34.496 --> 36:36.629
- Okay.

36:36.672 --> 36:38.283
Hey, it's okay. It's okay.

36:38.326 --> 36:39.719
It's okay. Come here.
- No.

36:39.762 --> 36:40.937
- Come on, don't do that.
Come here.

36:40.981 --> 36:42.243
You gotta let go.
You gotta let go.

36:42.287 --> 36:44.724
- Daddy, no.
- I want to stay with you.

36:44.767 --> 36:46.378
- You'll always gonna be
with me.

36:46.421 --> 36:47.596
Right here.

36:47.640 --> 36:49.424
You got that?

36:49.468 --> 36:51.600
You got that? Always.

36:51.644 --> 36:53.733
[sentimental music]

36:53.776 --> 36:57.258
Now look, y'all see that
nice young lady over there?

36:58.564 --> 37:00.479
You gonna run to her, okay?

37:00.522 --> 37:01.784
I know y'all like
to run with me

37:01.828 --> 37:03.743
in the backyard
when I'm practicing, right?

37:03.786 --> 37:05.092
Just pretend like
you're running with me

37:05.135 --> 37:06.659
in the backyard, okay?

37:06.702 --> 37:09.270
I need you to remember
that Daddy loves you.

37:09.314 --> 37:10.967
Daddy loves you so much.

37:12.969 --> 37:14.797
Daddy's always gonna love you.

37:14.841 --> 37:16.016
Okay?

37:17.800 --> 37:19.019
Come on.

37:22.414 --> 37:25.025
Okay.
All right, let's go. Okay.

37:25.068 --> 37:29.595
♪

37:29.638 --> 37:33.947
- Yes, sweetie, okay.
I got 'em.

37:33.990 --> 37:36.123
- Hey, hey, hey.
Hey, Sonny, don't you dare.

37:36.166 --> 37:37.646
You don't want to do that,
just like you didn't

37:37.690 --> 37:39.126
want to hurt Esme, right?

37:39.169 --> 37:41.433
- But I did. But I did.

37:41.476 --> 37:45.654
I hurt her. I hurt her.

37:45.698 --> 37:46.829
[voice breaking]
I hurt her.

37:46.873 --> 37:49.136
[tense music]

37:49.179 --> 37:51.051
I went home to surprise her.

37:51.094 --> 37:54.446
I went home to surprise her.
She loved surprises.

37:54.489 --> 37:56.926
But when I got home,
she wasn't there.

37:56.970 --> 37:58.493
So I thought--

38:00.669 --> 38:02.976
I thought--

38:03.019 --> 38:04.978
my--my head hurt--

38:05.021 --> 38:07.720
my head hurt from the game,
and I, um--

38:07.763 --> 38:09.678
my mind was so mixed up.

38:09.722 --> 38:12.464
I knew she'd been
celebrating her birthday.

38:12.507 --> 38:14.988
I know she--I knew
she'd been celebrating.

38:15.031 --> 38:18.165
And--and--and she had a knife,
I guess I forgot.

38:18.208 --> 38:19.558
'Cause she says,

38:19.601 --> 38:21.386
"Sonny,
what are you doing here?"

38:23.388 --> 38:26.434
So I figured maybe
she has someone else.

38:26.478 --> 38:29.045
I figured she had someone else.
She had a knife.

38:29.089 --> 38:31.831
So I grabbed the knife.
She tried to take it from me.

38:31.874 --> 38:34.399
My shoulder twisted,
and it hurt.

38:34.442 --> 38:36.705
And it hurt. And it hurt.

38:36.749 --> 38:39.404
And it hurt so bad.

38:39.447 --> 38:42.755
And I got angry and I got
so angry, and I don't know why.

38:42.798 --> 38:44.713
I don't know why.
Why did I do that?

38:44.757 --> 38:46.846
Why did I get so mad?
Why did I get so angry?

38:46.889 --> 38:49.501
- You weren't in your
right mind, Sonny.

38:49.544 --> 38:52.504
- I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

38:52.547 --> 38:56.072
I'm sorry, Esme. I'm sorry.

38:56.116 --> 38:58.466
- She knows.

38:58.510 --> 39:00.860
I promise she knows.

39:00.903 --> 39:03.645
She knows you're sorry.

39:03.689 --> 39:07.388
Bronson and Nash, they took
advantage of your sickness.

39:07.432 --> 39:08.694
Of you.

39:12.611 --> 39:14.700
- My team just arrested Nash.

39:14.743 --> 39:18.094
It's not justice for what
he did to you, not even close,

39:18.138 --> 39:21.663
but Nash and Bronson will never
be able to put another athlete

39:21.707 --> 39:23.186
through the agony
they've put you through.

39:23.230 --> 39:30.411
♪

39:31.673 --> 39:32.979
- Tell them to check my brain.

39:33.022 --> 39:35.155
[gunshot]
- Sonny, no!

39:35.198 --> 39:37.462
- Shots fired!
- No!

39:37.505 --> 39:39.551
- Oh, my God!

39:39.594 --> 39:42.554
[somber music]

39:42.597 --> 39:49.604
♪

39:54.827 --> 39:56.742
- Anything?

39:56.785 --> 39:58.004
- No.

40:00.093 --> 40:03.096
[Kristin sobbing]

40:09.972 --> 40:11.191
- It's okay.

40:14.237 --> 40:16.283
It's going to be okay.

40:16.326 --> 40:23.464
♪

40:30.123 --> 40:31.124
- Ingrid?

40:33.692 --> 40:34.867
I'm home.

40:38.784 --> 40:40.263
[phone buzzes]

41:19.694 --> 41:22.654
[sentimental music]

41:22.697 --> 41:29.704
♪

41:42.412 --> 41:43.370
- Hi.

41:43.413 --> 41:44.893
- Hi, Mom.
- Hi, kiddo.

41:44.937 --> 41:46.895
- Uh, hey, Kristin.
- Hey.

41:46.939 --> 41:50.203
- Um, this is my friend,
Meredith.

41:50.246 --> 41:52.814
- How are you?
- Nice to meet you.

41:52.858 --> 41:53.859
- Yeah.

41:55.251 --> 41:58.951
- So, uh, what are you doing?

41:58.994 --> 42:00.866
- Oh, I was just--
- Oh, crap. I forgot.

42:00.909 --> 42:03.869
I asked you to read
my essay tonight.

42:03.912 --> 42:05.435
- Yeah, but if it's not
a good time--

42:05.479 --> 42:08.090
- No, it is--let me get it,
and I'll meet you upstairs.

42:08.134 --> 42:11.659
Sorry, Mom. My bad.
- No, it's okay, kiddo.

42:11.703 --> 42:12.878
It's nice to meet you.

42:12.921 --> 42:14.880
And I'll see you later.

42:14.923 --> 42:21.930
♪

42:29.808 --> 42:32.767
[dramatic music]

42:32.811 --> 42:39.818
♪

42:49.828 --> 42:51.394
[wolf howls]
